Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["8. Summary", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"a1b2c3d4-0009-0001-0001-000000000001"],

Cell["\<\
This notebook computes the Eshelby depolarization tensor for a regular \
tetrahedron analytically, using Mathematica\[CloseCurlyQuote]s symbolic \
Integrate for both the surface integrals (Eshelby) and volume integrals \
(moments, g0).

Key results:
1. I_{ijkl} decomposes as A\[Delta]_{ij}\[Delta]_{kl} + B(\[Delta]_{ik}\
\[Delta]_{jl} + \[Delta]_{il}\[Delta]_{jk}) + C E_{ijkl}
   The SAME cubic structure as the cube \[Dash] T_d symmetry is sufficient.

2. The geometric integrals simplify completely (L = Log[Sqrt[2]+Sqrt[3]]):
   Ja_{kl} = -4Pi/3 * delta_{kl}  (universal for any convex body)
   Jb_{1122} = (6 Sqrt[2] L - 4 Pi - 12 Sqrt[3]) / 9
   Jb_{1212} = (6 Sqrt[2] L + 8 Pi - 12 Sqrt[3]) / 9
   Jb_{1111} = (-12 Sqrt[2] L - 4 Pi + 24 Sqrt[3]) / 9
   All involve the same transcendental L = Log[Sqrt[2]+Sqrt[3]] = ArcSinh[Sqrt[2]].
   Pell identities: Log[5-2Sqrt[6]] = -Log[5+2Sqrt[6]], etc.
   ArcTan identity: ArcTan[2Sqrt[2]-3Sqrt[3]] - ArcTan[2Sqrt[2]-Sqrt[3]]
                    + ArcTan[4Sqrt[2]+3Sqrt[3]] = -Pi/6.
   Moments S0, S1, S2, S11 are exact rationals.

3. The entire compute_cube_tmatrix machinery (T1, T2, T3, amplification \
factors, effective contrasts) transfers directly to the tetrahedron with only \
numerical constants changed.

4. C_tet is much smaller than C_cube, confirming the tet is more isotropic \
(closer to a sphere) than the cube.

5. g0_tet = 4 Sqrt[2] Log[Sqrt[2] + Sqrt[3]] - 2 Pi/3.
   Equivalent forms: 4 Sqrt[2] ArcSinh[Sqrt[2]] - 2 Pi/3
                     (2/3)(Sqrt[2] Log[485 + 198 Sqrt[6]] - Pi)
   The Pell connection 485^2 - 6 * 198^2 = 1 parallels the cube result.
   Proved by PSLQ + analytical derivation (volume-to-surface reduction,
   complex partial fractions with denesting Sqrt[7+4i Sqrt[2]] = 2Sqrt[2]+i,
   and miraculous ArcTan cancellations). See scripts/g0_tet_sympy_v4.py.

   Compare: g0_cube = (4/3) Log[70226 + 40545 Sqrt[3]] - 2 Pi.
   Both have the structure A * Log[algebraic] - B * Pi.
   Cube lives in Q(Sqrt[3]), tet in Q(Sqrt[2], Sqrt[3]) = Q(Sqrt[6]).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"a1b2c3d4-0009-0001-0001-000000000002"]
